rComments: She is BY FAR the most caring and understanding prof I have ever had. There is a lot of content (long lectures, textbook, additional readings, discussion posts weekly) but it is very possible to do well. She is very woke and a SJW so keep that in mind depending on if you like that or not because it is very apparent in material and discussions.

seriously one of the most down-to-earth chill kind and just real teachers. no bs just taught the reality of psychopathology with all its good and bads there was no hierarchy felt like i was learning from a friend i had a lot of respect for. lots of participation for class... the assignments I learned a lot from and actually found helpful
The class was super great despite being online. She was super understand of the struggles of being a student during the pandemic. Great class great teacher.

Amazing class! Her dad died in the middle of the semester and everything had to change but always to our benefit and ended up being easier for us in the end. Always felt comfortable to approach her and ask questions, extremely flexible and understanding of the current situation never asked for sick notes etc.

Noor is super sweet, one of the most understanding profs in uni hands down. She approached the course from a clinical& real-world perspective, its the most I've learned about psychology application to real life in any course on top of that she taught us about how society/social problems impact mental health which I never considered before.
